Head
(
Fig. 1F
, 

2I

) with broad triangular rostrum, protruding downward; rostrum tip varies from acute to slightly truncated. Head keel very wide; distance from eye to the keel margin about 3–4 diameters of eye. Ocellus smaller than eye; distance from tip of rostrum to ocellus two times greater than distance between ocellus and eye. Three connected major head pores located at flattened portion of dorsal keel (
Fig. 2E
); РР about 0.5 IР. Lateral pores minute, located at about 1.5 IР distance from midline. Labrum (
Fig. 3A–B, J
) smaller than in other species of the genus. Labral keel moderately wide (height about 1.7–2 widths), with blunt or broadly rounded apex. Anterior margin from polygonal to regularly convex; posterior margin convex, with 2 clusters of short setulae.

Male.
Body low oval (
Fig.1M
), with well developed dorsal keel on head and valves; height/length ratio about 0.55; maximum height at the second quarter of the body. Body strongly compressed laterally. Head (
Fig. 1N
) with truncated rostrum. Ocellus and eye of same proportions as in female.
